# Dual publish (factory maintainer)

**Authority:** [.cursor/plans/dual-publish-architecture.md](../plans/dual-publish-architecture.md)

## What ships

- **`github-publish-lisp/cursor-landing-skill/`** — **v3 ship product** (pseudo-Lisp). Own git repo → [cursor-landing-v3](https://github.com/rphoward/cursor-landing-v3). Factory `.gitignore` excludes this folder from main commits. Workflow: [docs/FACTORY-V3-WORKFLOW.md](../../docs/FACTORY-V3-WORKFLOW.md).
- **Factory root** + **`github-publish/`** (after build) — markdown + JSON variant (`/cursor-landing`).

These are **parallel products**, not one folder overwritten by the other.

## When editing under `github-publish-lisp/`

1. **Do not** replace `SKILL.md`, `question-bank.md`, or `scan-checklist.md` with copies from factory root — they must stay **pseudo-Lisp** per [BUNDLE-MANIFEST.md](../../github-publish-lisp/cursor-landing-skill/BUNDLE-MANIFEST.md).
2. **Do** port new behavior (grill questions, annex paths, MERGE sections) into the correct format; run `python github-publish-lisp/check-parens.py` before calling Lisp bundle work done.
3. Markdown annexes (`references/annexes/*.md`, `MERGE-TO-RULES.md`) may align with factory text but must use **Lisp bundle** links (no `AGENT-FORENSICS-RESEARCH-RESULTS.md` unless that file exists in the Lisp tree).
4. Prefer `git checkout <lisp-commit> -- path` + forward port over wholesale copy from `SKILL.md` at repo root.

## When editing factory `references/` or root `SKILL.md`

If the change affects scan/grill behavior for **both** variants, plan a **second pass** on the Lisp tree — `build-install-bundle.ps1` does **not** update `github-publish-lisp/`.
